Parliament, Monday, 5 March 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow hold a hearing with the National Treasury on the Integrated Financial Management System (IFMS). Details of the meeting: Date: Tuesday, 6 March 2018
	Time: 09:00
	Venue: V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building Meanwhile, Scopa will receive a briefing from Eskom on defaulting municipalities tomorrow evening. Details of the meeting: Date: Tuesday, 6 March 2018
	Time: 18:00
	Venue: V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI. For media enquiries, please contact the Committee’s Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
